North Rift Jubilee Party women governor hopefuls have expressed fears over nominations, citing threats and intimidation from male rivals.The aspirants said men have huge resources, which they use to scare them from campaigning. They spoke during a workshop for women hopefuls from Uasin Gishu, Trans Nzoia and Nandi counties at an Eldoret hotel. The forum was organised by the Federation of Women Lawyers in partnership with the Media Focus in Africa.Participants expressed reservations over the manner in which JP nominations will be conducted, saying they might not be free and fair. Nandi hopeful Mitei Cheruiyot said their male rivals plan to skew nomination results in their favour. Despite the limited resources, we are determined to go on and campaign on equal platform with them, she said.